Executive Profile
Sandy J. Masselli Jr.Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, Carlyle Entertainment Ltd.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships53--
Background

		Mr. Sandy J. Masselli, Jr. has been the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of Carlyle Entertainment Ltd. (formerly Carlyle Gaming & Entertainments Ltd.) since May 15, 2008. Mr. Masselli has been Managing Director of Intercapital Asset Management Company Inc. since May 1990. Mr. Masselli is responsible for the selection and monitoring of investments as well as merchant banking activities at Intercapital Asset Management. He serves as the Chief Executive Officer of International ... Apparel Group Inc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of SWAV Enterprises Ltd. until December 2009. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Total Apparel Group Inc. since January 23, 1998 and as its President from January 1998 to January 2005. From May 1981 to May 1990, Mr. Masselli served as President or Senior Vice President at several major securities and brokerage firms, including Prudential Securities, Inc., Drexel Burnham Lambert, Inc., Shearson Lehman Hutton, Inc. and Merrill Lynch Pierce Fenner & Smith, Inc. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Total Entertainment Inc. from 1996 to 2006. He served as Chairman and Director of Total Apparel Group Inc.(formerly, Total Luxury Group Inc.) since January 21, 1998. He has been a Director at Carlyle Gaming & Entertainments Ltd., May 15, 2008. He served as a Director of SWAV Enterprises Ltd. until December 2009. Mr. Masselli holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science from Monmouth College and a Juris Doctor from LaSalle University.Read Full Background




