t and the disbursement of checks. In the Canadian lawsuit, The Supreme Court for the District of Quebec issued a Writ of Pre Judgment against these two individuals and has located $500,000.00 in assets that are the property of Sandy J. Masselli, Jr., but placed by these two individuals in a separate account that they controlled.Carlyle's legal counsel had advised the Company that the criminal charge of check kiting requires control of two bank accounts by a single person in order to be applicable. With regard to the two accounts that were involved in the matter, Sandy J. Masselli, Jr., did not have control of any kind with regard to one of them. The account over which he had no control was an account that was opened by two other individuals, giving them sole and complete control. Therefore, the legal theory of the indictment was not applicable.A debt to a creditor is a civil matter, not a criminal matter. Moreover, the involved entity bank which owed Sandy J. Masselli, Jr., a great deal more than he owed to them. All of which was resolved in a civil matter in the Superior Court of New Jersey.ReblogShareTweetShareRecently ViewedYour list is empty.What to Read NextObamacare is hurting these people—and Congress is doing nothing about itYahoo FinanceToday's charts: Alphabet earnings in focus; Nvidia gets a bullish call; Blue Apron shares soarYahoo FinanceDemocrats roll out another feeble economic planYahoo FinanceJared Kushner sealed real estate deal with oligarch's firm cited in money-laundering caseThe GuardianChina is crushing American tech titansYahoo Finance VideoStocks rangebound ahead of big earningsYahoo FinanceWall Street can't save Blue Apron's stockYahoo FinanceTrump lashes out at his 'beleaguered' attorney general and asks why he isn't investigating Clinton's emails and Russia connectionsBusiness InsiderNasdaq hits record ahead of big tech earnings; Dow, S&P lagReutersSamsung Bioepis launches U.S. sales of Remicade biosmiliarReutersGoogle's forward guidance 